<sect1 id="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para><graphic fileref="figures/gnome-ding.png" format="PNG"></graphic></para> 
   
<para>
        &app; is a grafical tool for spellchecking and translation for Gnome2.
        &app; was intended by ding (http://www-user.tu-chemnitz.de/~fri/ding/)
</para>
<para>
        &app; will use egrep and a ispell/aspell dictionary as backend.
</para>

<para>
        &app; work with <acronym>Gtk2+</acronym> and <acronym>GNOME2</acronym>. 
        &app; required as backend aspell (0.50) und grep (2.5.x).
</para>

</sect1> <!-- id=introduction -->

<!-- ################################################################# -->
<sect1 id="getting-started">
<title>Getting started with &app;</title>
<para><graphic fileref="figures/gnome-ding.png" format="PNG"></graphic></para> 

<sect2 id="getting-started-gnome-ding-to-start">
       <title>To start &app;</title>
       <para>You can start <application>&app;</application> in the following ways:</para>
          <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                <term><guimenu>Application</guimenu> menu</term>
                <listitem>
                <para>Choose <menuchoice><guisubmenu>Accessories</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>gnome-ding</guimenuitem>
                </menuchoice>. </para>
                </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                <term>Or bye using Command line </term>
                <listitem>
                <para>Type <programlisting>gnome-ding</programlisting>then press <keycap>Return</keycap>.
		</para>
		</listitem>
                </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
	<para>
	If you start &app; now at first time, then all nesseccary configurations will be make automaticly.
	</para>	

</sect2> <!-- gnome-ding-to-start -->

