<sect2 id="win-main-menubar">
   <title>Menubar</title>
   <para>
   The menus on the menubar contain all of the commands you need to work with &app;.
   </para>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="win-main-commandbar">
   <title>Commandbar</title>
   <para>
   The Commandbar contain all possible commands of &app; for searching and selecting a dictionary.
   In the editable  'Search' you can input your word where you wish to lookup for in the dictionary.
   Byside you will can selected the dictionary, where you want to use for the lookup, like spelling in
   German or translation.
   </para>
   <para>
   For start the lookup, press the 'Search'-Button on the commandbar or choose 'search from the menubar.
   </para>
</sect2>



<sect2 id="win-main-result">
    <title>Result-Window</title>
    <para>
    The Result-Windows will shown the result of the lookup for the defined word. 
    </para>

    <para>    
    If you use a dictionary for spellchecking, then the result-window will show, if the word will be found.
    If the spelling are incorrect or unknown, then the result-window will contain some suggestions for
    the correct spelling, if aspell will have found someone.
    </para>

    <para>
    If you use the ding-dictionary for translation, i.e. german to english, the result-window will shown the
    matching results for the defined search-word. The results will shown as a list of matches. In the list,
    you will find some spezials abbreviation. This abbreviations give a better describe for the matched entries,
    like the sex of the word, or the typical usage or the special branches.
    </para>

</sect2>

<sect2 id="win-main-statusbar">
   <title>Statusbar</title>
   <para>
   The statusbar at the bottom of the window will displays information about current &app; 
   activity and contextual information. This can be a error messages or the number of search results. 
   </para>
</sect2>

</sect1>









