<sect1 id="win-usage">
<title>Usage</title>
<para><graphic fileref="figures/gnome-ding.png" format="PNG"></graphic></para> 

<para>
The usage of &app; is very easy. First you will input your interrested word into the
search entry. After you have now input your search-string, please select the prefered
dictionary to use for the search. Then press the search-button on the serachbar.
In the follow &app; will display in the result-window the results (as a list) for
your search request.
</para>

<para>
Please remember, &app; is not developed to check or translate sentences. 
</para>

<para>
Please remember, &app; is developed to work offline. You must have installed the
prefered dictionaries. Typical, all neccessary dictonaries will be installed on
your linux-box, if you use Gnome2 and have installed &app; correctly.
</para>
 
</sect1>  <!-- usage -->


