<!--  SECTION: Known Bugs and Limitations -->
<sect1 id="win-bugs">
<title>Limitations</title>
  <para><graphic fileref="figures/gnome-ding.png" format="PNG"></graphic></para> 

<para>
&app; use als backend for spellchecking aspell. &app; will use the C-API to aspell, so &app; can
use aspell directly. But if you have install a newer version of aspell, perhaps with a other
A-API interface design, than &app; will not work correct. Also I have no idea, if my implementation
will also work correct with some special charsets, like KO8 or japanese. This must be tested be
some people, who understand this language.
</para>

<para>
Also &app; use for translation a ding-dictionary. The search will use only egrep for search of matched
strings. But it will not know something about the semantic of a lookup. So the search-result is not
the best one. Also the ding-dictionary is converted to the UFT8-Charset. This is a little better for
special chars an I front of the extension to other languages, but grep will work very slow with
utf8-coded files.
</para>

<para>
If some people have a solve for this problen, in detail also for the usage of good offline dictionaries
in multi-languages, please be free and send a email to the author. Also you can use this source-code
and develop a better program under the terms of the GNU GPL2.
</para>
</sect1>  <!-- bugs -->

